{
  "text": "In this study, \u03b1-amylase was employed to enhance protein extraction yield. [CITATION_1] reported that \u03b1-amylase was more effective than other carbohydrates for protein extraction. As shown in Figure 2 , the yield of protein extraction increased to 72.18% with \u03b1-amylase pretreatment (1 800 unit/g DRSF, 6 h) which is significantly (P = 0.001) higher than that without \u03b1-amylase pretreatment (52.24%). [CITATION_2] reported that the protein yield of heat-stabilized defatted rice bran can be increased from 11.7% to 37.3% by using higher amount of \u03b1-amylase (2 200 unit/g heat-stabilized defatted rice bran). The higher amount of food-grade \u03b1-amylase required in the work of [CITATION_3] was caused by contamination of enzyme by protease.",
  "citation_candidates": [
    "84244662",
